HEADWORD: Effervescent
<hw>Ef`fer*ves"cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>effervescences</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>effervescere</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>effervescent</ets>.]</ety> <def>Gently boiling or bubbling, by
means of the disengagement of gas</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Effervescible</ent>⟦br⟧
